# claw-linux crontab — managed by claw-cron
# Format: MIN HOUR MDAY MON WDAY COMMAND
# Specials: @reboot @daily @hourly @weekly @monthly
# Step syntax: */N means "every N units" (e.g. */5 in MIN = every 5 minutes)
#
# Edit this file to add automated tasks.
# Send SIGHUP to claw-cron to reload without restarting.

# ── Health checks ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Log a heartbeat every 5 minutes (note: */5 step syntax is supported)
# */5 * * * * echo "{\"command\":\"echo claw-cron heartbeat\",\"timeout\":5}" | /usr/local/bin/claw-shell >> /var/lib/claw/cron.log 2>&1

# ── Memory maintenance ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Summarise and compact memory daily at 02:00
# 0 2 * * * python3 /opt/claw/agent/main.py "Summarise today's memory into key facts and forget verbose conversation history"

# ── Startup ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tasks to run once when the system boots
# @reboot python3 /opt/claw/agent/main.py "System started. Run self-check and report status."
